Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
dumpPictures(25.10)                                        dumpPictures(25.10)

Name
       dumpPictures - Dumps images at various stages of the Innovus flow (such
       as  congestion map, cell density map, floorplan view, colored hierarchy
       map), when executed in batch mode

Syntax
       dumpPictures

       [-help]

       -dir <string>[-fullScreen]

       -prefix <string>

       Dumps images at various stages of the Innovus flow (such as  congestion
       map, cell density map, floorplan view, colored hierarchy map), when ex-
       ecuted  in  batch  mode. This command dumps the following images in the
       specified directory in the .gif format:

              * ctd

              * congestion

              * density

              * floor

              * placement

              * route_all

              * route_C4

              * route_C5

              * route_C6

              * route_M1

              * route_M2

              * route_M3

              * specialroute

              * violations

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each dumpPictures parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man dumpPictures

       -dir <string>
              Specifies the output directory.

       -fullScreen
              Maximizes the window.

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies the file prefix.

Example
       The following command dumps the  full  screen  images  at  the  various
       stages of the Innovus flow to the TEST directory:

       dumpPictures -dir TEST -prefix [dbGet top.name] -fullScreen

       The following images are dumped in the TEST directory:

              * congestion

              * density

              * floor

              * placement

              * route_all

              * route_C4

              * route_C5

              * route_C6

              * route_M1

              * route_M2

              * route_M3

              * specialroute

              * violations

